AMR RAMSES example
==================

Files
-----
  ramses_snap10.in    Template input file for a RAMSES snapshot

Usage
-----
1. Edit ramses_snap10.in:
   - Set par%amr_file    = '/path/to/ramses_run'
   - Set par%amr_snapnum = <output number>

2. Run:
   mpirun -np 8 ../../LaRT.x ramses_snap10.in

RAMSES directory structure expected
-------------------------------------
  <amr_file>/output_<NNNNN>/
      info_<NNNNN>.txt
      amr_<NNNNN>.out00001  ...  amr_<NNNNN>.out<NCPU>
      hydro_<NNNNN>.out00001 ... hydro_<NNNNN>.out<NCPU>

  where NNNNN = par%amr_snapnum zero-padded to 5 digits.

Hydro variable layout assumed
-------------------------------
  Variable 1: density (code units)
  Variables 2-4: momentum (rho*vx, rho*vy, rho*vz)
  Variable 5: total energy (or pressure)
  Variable 6: metallicity (optional, not used by LaRT)

  Unit scales (unit_l, unit_d, unit_t) are read from info_NNNNN.txt.

Neutral fraction
----------------
  par%use_cie_condition = .true.   (recommended for cosmological runs)
      nHI/nH estimated from nH and T using collisional-ionisation equilibrium.

  par%use_cie_condition = .false.  (default)
      All hydrogen assumed neutral.  Only appropriate for cold ISM runs.

Opacity normalisation
---------------------
  par%taumax  > 0   : rescale so that tau_pole = par%taumax
  par%N_HImax > 0   : rescale to target column density [cm^-2]
  Both <= 0         : use raw physical densities from RAMSES (recommended
                      for real simulations where nHI is already physical)
